# Plokitch Unified Architecture & Integration Blueprint

This document serves as the official decision plan for unifying the Plokitch Web App and Admin Dashboard into a single-source-of-truth ecosystem.

---

## 1. System Classification Map

| Feature Area | Classification | System Ownership | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Discovery (Search/Map)** | WEB-ONLY | Web App | Primary consumer entry point. |
| **Ordering & Checkout** | WEB-ONLY | Web App | Transaction initiation layer. |
| **Consumer Tracking** | WEB-ONLY | Web App | Read-only state for users. |
| **Global Dispatch Control**| ADMIN-ONLY | Dashboard | Operational override and queue management. |
| **Global Analytics** | ADMIN-ONLY | Dashboard | Executive-level platform intelligence. |
| **Financial Reconciliation**| ADMIN-ONLY | Dashboard | Payouts, audits, and revenue tracking. |
| **Support & Complaints** | ADMIN-ONLY | Dashboard | Manual conflict resolution layer. |
| **Authentication** | SHARED CORE | Unified Auth | Single Identity across all platforms. |
| **Order/Vendor Data** | SHARED CORE | Unified API | Shared schemas for consistency. |
| **Legacy Admin Pages** | **LEGACY** | **REMOVE** | `apps/web/src/pages/admin/*` |

---

## 2. Truth Ownership Matrix

| Data Entity | Primary Owner | Secondary Access (Read) | Modification Authority |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Order State** | Unified Backend | Web (Tracking) | Dashboard (Full Override) |
| **Vendor Status** | Unified Backend | Web (Profile) | Dashboard (Verification/Suspension) |
| **User Identity** | Supabase Auth | Both | Dashboard (Global Management) |
| **Payment Records** | Unified Backend | Web (History) | Dashboard (Auditing/Reconciliation) |

---

## 3. Deprecation & Removal Plan (The "Cleanup")

To eliminate "split-brain" architecture and data duplication, the following assets must be removed or redirected:

### 🗑️ Files to Remove (Web App)
- `apps/web/src/pages/admin/` (Full directory delete)
- `apps/web/src/pages/admin/AdminAnalytics.tsx`
- `apps/web/src/pages/admin/UserManagement.tsx`
- `apps/web/src/pages/admin/OrderOverview.tsx`
- `apps/web/src/pages/admin/AdminSettings.tsx`
- `apps/web/src/pages/admin/AdminPanel.tsx`

### 🔄 Route Redirections
- Any request to `/admin/*` on the Web App domain should be server-side redirected (301) to the dedicated Dashboard domain (e.g., `admin.plokitch.com`).

---

## 4. Integration Strategy

### A. API Consolidation
- **Uniformity**: Transition from the ephemeral `:4000` assumptions to a production-ready API gateway.
- **Protocol**: Standardize on a unified REST or GraphQL schema that both apps consume.
- **Clients**: Move all data fetching logic to a shared `@plokitch/api-client` to prevent schema drift.

### B. Auth Unification (RBAC)
- **Single Sign-On (SSO)**: Implement a unified Supabase Auth layer.
- **Roles**:
  - `CUSTOMER`: Access to Web App only.
  - `VENDOR`: Access to Web (Kitchen Management) + Limited Dashboard views.
  - `ADMIN`: Full access to Dashboard; restricted to user views on Web.

---

## 5. Final Unified Architecture Blueprint

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Experience Layer (Frontend)"
        WA[Plokitch Web App]
        AD[Admin Dashboard]
    end

    subgraph "Integration Layer"
        API[Unified API Gateway]
        AUTH[Unified Auth / RBAC]
    end

    subgraph "Data Layer (Source of Truth)"
        DB[(Supabase / Postgres)]
    end

    WA --> API
    WA --> AUTH
    AD --> API
    AD --> AUTH
    API --> DB
    AUTH --> DB
```

